dataSources: Farmers' Market Data: U.S. Department of Agriculture, May 2018.
description: Increased access to fresh produce for low-income Americans is an explicit priority of the Department of Agriculture (Food and Nutrition Service, U.S. Department of Agriculture). While there are certainly other retailers that sell fresh produce and accept SNAP payments, farmers' markets provide healthy, locally-grown foods at lower prices than supermarkets (The Atlantic). Use this map to explore the accessibility of these markets to the general public.
name: SNAP-Friendly Farmers' Markets
subtitle: Vendors that accept Supplemental Nutrition Assistance Program benefits
